<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-02-23T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-02-23T19:00:00-05:00" n="384" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d384">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 818.00/90a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Minister <persName type="to">Leavell</persName>
                            </hi><note n="4" xml:id="d384fn4">Same to the American Legations at
                                Managua, Tegucigalpa and San Salvador.</note>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-02-23T19:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">February 23, 1917, 7 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>The following statement has been made to General Tinoco at San José and
                            he has been informed that it has been made public in the United States
                            and in Central America: [Here follows second paragraph of above
                            telegram.]</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>